Intersil Announces Appointment of Roger Wendelken as Senior Vice President of Worldwide Sales
Photos(1)Documents(1)



Roger Wendelken was appointed as Intersil's Senior Vice President of Worldwide Sales on Monday, October 14th.
Sep 2, 2014
Download: Hi Res (40 KB)




View PDF VersionTuesday, September 2, 2014 (3:38pm)

CLOSE

MILPITAS, Calif., Oct. 14, 2013 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- Intersil Corporation (Nasdaq:ISIL), a leading provider of innovative power management and precision analog solutions, today announced the appointment of Roger Wendelken as senior vice president of worldwide sales effective immediately. Mr. Wendelken brings valuable experience managing global sales organizations, increasing market share in key accounts and developing and growing distribution channels.
A photo accompanying this release is available at http://www.globenewswire.com/newsroom/prs/?pkgid=21493
"Intersil has a strong technical heritage and a growing portfolio of differentiated products," said Necip Sayiner, president and CEO of Intersil Corporation. "Roger will play a key role in driving sustainable revenue growth as we continue to hone our portfolio. We're very pleased to have a sales executive with his experience join our team."
"This is a great time to be part of the sales organization at Intersil, a company focused on winning in key markets through innovation," said Mr. Wendelken. "I look forward to working with the management team to enable our customers' success and grow the business."
Mr. Wendelken has more than 20 years of sales experience in the semiconductor industry. He was most recently the senior vice president of worldwide sales for Volex Corporation. Previously he led the global sales organization for SMSC before it was acquired by Microchip, building a presence in a variety of competitive consumer, industrial and automotive markets. Mr. Wendelken also served as vice president of worldwide sales at AMCC and Marvell, where under his leadership, the sales team secured market share against larger competitors in key enterprise networking accounts. Mr. Wendelken holds a BSEE from the Georgia Institute of Technology.
About Intersil
Intersil Corporation is a leading provider of innovative power management and precision analog solutions. The company's products address some of the largest markets within the industrial and infrastructure, mobile computing and high-end consumer markets. For more information about Intersil, visit our website at www.intersil.com.
Intersil and the Intersil logo are trademarks or registered trademarks of Intersil Corporation. All other brands, product names and marks are or may be trademarks or registered trademarks used to identify products or services of their respective owners.
CONTACT: Media Contact:
         Shannon Pleasant
         Intersil Corporation
         (512) 382-8444
         spleasant@intersil.com

